  "data": {
    "description": {
      "value": "<p><strong>Element&nbsp;</strong>water;&nbsp;<strong>Type&nbsp;</strong>utility (Sp);&nbsp;<strong>Level&nbsp;</strong>3;&nbsp;<strong>Burn&nbsp;</strong>0<br><strong>Prerequisite&nbsp;</strong>kinetic cover<br><strong>Saving Throw&nbsp;</strong>none; see text;&nbsp;<strong>SR&nbsp;</strong>no</p>\n<p>You can manipulate massive quantities of water. As a standard action, you can raise or lower the level of water as if using @Compendium[pf1.spells.7yf67b7y4byj96w7]{Control Water}, or move an amount of water equal to 1/1,000th the amount controlled by that spell to a different location in range. The water remains where you placed it for as long as you remain motionless and take a standard action each round to concentrate on this effect. This wild talent causes a slow effect on creatures made of water, just like control water (Will negates).</p>\n<p>When you cease concentrating, the water flows normally unless you accept 1 point of burn to extend the duration and hold the water in its current position for 10 minutes per kineticist level you possess.</p>",
